And if your budget allows it and you find the information at xwordinfo.com interesting, it’s well worth supporting. 

I’m an occasional anonymous contributor there: If I solve a puzzle from the archives that predates Wordplay and that has a difficult-to-grasp theme, I’ll suggest to Jim Horne that he consider adding an explanatory note. Jim seems like a nice guy; he’s always responded promptly and positively to my suggestions.

